<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 15 at 4:57AM EST  by NWS Chicago</headline>
<description>...Slippery Roads Early this Morning...
The light accumulating snow from last night and early this
morning has left a coating across many roads, parking lots, and
sidewalks. In addition, there was patchy freezing drizzle early
this morning in some places. With temperatures falling through the
rest of the early morning and remaining well below freezing,
slick spots will continue several hours after daybreak.
Allow extra travel time and use heightened caution this morning
due to the slippery road conditions. Keep plenty of following
distance behind other vehicles.</description>
